if they went into
places like California,

00:46:22.074 --> 00:46:22.990
that was a no-brainer.

00:46:22.990 --> 00:46:26.870
And plus, that permanently
kind of unshackled the family,

00:46:26.870 --> 00:46:29.690
if you will, and extended
family, if you will.

00:46:29.690 --> 00:46:33.620
And so when he said he
didn't want to kind of scale,

00:46:33.620 --> 00:46:34.780
then I said, OK.

00:46:34.780 --> 00:46:36.490
Why don't we just
clone his model?

00:46:36.490 --> 00:46:39.670
So I asked him if he had
any concern with me cloning.

00:46:39.670 --> 00:46:41.380
He said, no, that's great.

00:46:41.380 --> 00:46:41.950
Feel free.

00:46:41.950 --> 00:46:43.700
I'll try to help you, as well.

00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:46.750
And so that's what Dakshana
was set up as a vehicle

00:46:46.750 --> 00:46:49.540
to try to clone Super 30.

00:46:49.540 --> 00:46:55.360
And what we do is we basically
identify kids who are poor

00:46:55.360 --> 00:46:58.290
but they're very
talented, very gifted.

00:46:58.290 --> 00:47:03.250
And in India, if you
get a kid into IAT,

00:47:03.250 --> 00:47:06.839
there's a very high government
subsidy, probably an 80%, 90%

00:47:06.839 --> 00:47:07.630
government subsidy.

00:47:07.630 --> 00:47:10.540
So the education is
almost free, just

00:47:10.540 --> 00:47:14.410
a few thousand dollars, or
probably like $2,000 a year

00:47:14.410 --> 00:47:15.510
is what you pay.

00:47:15.510 --> 00:47:17.260
And even that you can
get loans and so on.

00:47:17.260 --> 00:47:25.300
So the easiest way to
lift a family from poverty

00:47:25.300 --> 00:47:29.710
is if there's high IQ in that
family, you can get into IAT

00:47:29.710 --> 00:47:32.070
and then get them out.

00:47:32.070 --> 00:47:36.100
So Dakshana has sent about--

00:47:36.100 --> 00:47:41.930
north of 1,000 kids so far have
cracked the IAT entrance exam,

00:47:41.930 --> 00:47:44.290
been accepted by the IATs.

00:47:44.290 --> 00:47:48.010
And now we have about 70% of
our kids every year who make it

00:47:48.010 --> 00:47:49.010
through, which is great.

00:47:49.010 --> 00:47:54.680
And so we have about 800
or so kids in our program

00:47:54.680 --> 00:47:57.120
at any given time and
we are scaling it up.

00:47:57.120 --> 00:48:00.560
I think by next year,
we'll be at over 1,100

00:48:00.560 --> 00:48:02.102
and then we'll keep
going from there.

00:48:02.102 --> 00:48:02.935
SAURABH MADAAN: Wow.

00:48:02.935 --> 00:48:04.100
Congratulations on that.

00:48:04.100 --> 00:48:05.330
MOHNISH PABRAI: Well,
there's a great team.

00:48:05.330 --> 00:48:06.080
It works out well.

00:48:06.080 --> 00:48:07.079
SAURABH MADAAN: Awesome.

